@{b}Starting Universal Translator@{ub}



This program may be started from the Workbench or the Shell window.


This program will detach from the Shell so you need not use Run or any
other variant.  There are a few command line arguments you may use when loading:



@{b}CDF/K@{ub}

The catalog description file to be converted.


@{b}CATALOG/K@{ub}

The output catalog, either internal or external.


@{b}PROTO/K@{ub}

String prototypes for use in a GST or other similar manner.

Only use with C output language.


@{b}BLANK/K@{ub}

Blank catalog description file.


@{b}TYPE/K@{ub}

Specify internal or external catalog.

TYPE=INTERNAL or TYPE=EXTERNAL.

Default INTERNAL


@{b}UNDEFINEDS/K@{ub}

Notify user if a string is undefined and abort.

UNDEFINEDS=TRUE or UNDEFINEDS=FALSE.

Default FALSE.


@{b}TABSIZE/K@{ub}

Specify tab size to use for output source code.  1-16 spaces.

TABSIZE=4

Default 4.


@{b}INFO/S@{ub}

Display information about the catalog.


@{b}ICONIFY/S@{ub}

Start in iconified mode.


@{b}ICON_X/K@{ub}

X coordinate for AppIcon.


@{b}ICON_Y/K@{ub}

Y coordinate for AppIcon.


@{b}PUBSCREEN/K@{ub}

Name of public screen to open the interface on.


@{b}LANGUAGE/K@{ub}

Preferred locale strings language.

Language must be all lower case.


@{b}UI/K@{ub}

Open or keep the user interface closed.

UI=TRUE or UI=FALSE.


@{b}NOVERSION/S@{ub}

Do not display program title when not using the editor.


@{b}DONOTDETACH/S@{ub}

Do not detach from the Shell.

Useful for SMake files.



The arguments are not case sensitive and may be mixed in any order.

ex: UniversalTranslator TYPE=EXTERNAL CDF Program.cd CATALOG CATALOGS:deutsch/Program.catalog


