@{b}Operation Notes@{ub}



Press the Help key for AmigaGuide help.


It can be started in WBStartup and iconified so it is always available.


A semi-colon as the first character designates a comment.


Backslash sequences, such as: \\n, \\e, \\0 count as one character.
\\xHH counts as two.


Splitting a long line into multiple lines will make it easier to read and
translate.  Use a backslash as the last character for each line to signal more
line.


When making an external catalog, Universal Translator will automatically
go to the correct language directory in CATALOGS:, i.e., CATALOGS:deutsch, or
whatever language the catalog is translated in.


