@NODE HintsAndTips "Hints And Tips"
@TOC Main
@{LINDENT 1}

@{b}Hints And Tips@{ub}



Grouping and naming strings according to their source module will make
updating much easier.


Splitting a long line into multiple lines will make it easier to read and
translate.  Use a backslash as the last character for each line to signal more
line.


Do not put a minimum or maximum length on a string unless absolutely
necessary.  The user interface should adjust to the strings, not the strings
to the user interface.


Universal Translator can easily be put into an SMakefile to update the
strings automatically.


When strings are added to a catalog, all the source code modules must be
re-compiled so the string number are changed.  If a program has no locale
strings in it, then name the object module with the suffix '.oo', and objects
modules with locale strings with the standard '.o' suffix.  Then just
delete #?.o, and you only have to re-compile the modules that have locale
strings.


@ENDNODE


